  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "Credibility assessment for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump intended for ventricular assist device (VAD) support. The simulation model predicts absolute hemolysis index (HI) under physiological flow conditions representative of a Class III implantable VAD operating at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; seven factors were formally assessed and six were scoped under epistemic-gap flags consistent with MRL 5 requirements. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was applied to boundary conditions and material parameters. The intended patient population comprises adults with end-stage heart failure; operating envelope is 3–6 L/min cardiac output at 60–120 mmHg pressure rise. Assessment outcome: Accepted under Minimal profile with documented credibility factor gaps acknowledged in the decision record.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cfd-hi-prediction-class3-vad",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis",
